Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- A UNIAN correspondent has learned that the 
composition of the official state delegation to the United 
States was finally confirmed on 2 March. Apart from President 
Leonid Kravchuk, the delegation will include Yukhym Zvyahilskyy, 
acting prime minister; Anatoliy Zlenko, minister of foreign 
affairs; Yevhen Marchuk, head of Ukraine's Security Service; 
Hryhoriy Pyatachenko, minister of finance; Vitaliy Radetskyy, 
minister of defense; Oleh Slyepichev, minister of external 
economic relations and trade; Roman Shpek, minister of economic 
affairs; Yuriy Karasyk, minister of agriculture; Ivan Dotsenko, 
minister to the Cabinet of Ministers; Viktor Yushchenko, 
National Bank chairman; and Anton Buteyko, the president's 
adviser on foreign policy issues. The editors of almost all the 
influential Ukrainian newspapers will also be in the delegation. 

